[Nouns] brown, brunet, brunette.
[Pigments] bister, ocher, sepia, Vandyke brown.
[Verbs] render brown; tan, embrown, bronze.
[Adjectives] brown, bay, dapple, auburn, castaneous, chestnut, nut-brown, cinnamon, russet, tawny, fuscous, chocolate, maroon, foxy, tan, brunette, whitey brown; fawn-colored, snuff-colored, liver-colored; brown as a berry, brown as mahogany, brown as the oak leaves; khaki.
sun-burnt, sunburned, tawny; tanned.
